   "body" : "I get errors from net.cpp and other modules (see below) about INT64_MIN and other constants not being defined. Including &lt;inttypes.h&gt;, &lt;stdint.h&gt;, or &lt;limits.h&gt; doesn't help, and neither does #defining __STDC_LIMIT_MACROS. These headers seem to work differently in C++ from C.\r\n\r\nTo make the modules compile, I had to write a header that #defines these constants in terms of the C++ numeric_limits template:\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n#ifndef CPPLIMITS_H\r\n#define CPPLIMITS_H\r\n#include &lt;limits&gt;\r\n#include &lt;inttypes.h&gt;\r\n#define INT64_MAX std::numeric_limits&lt;int64&gt;::max()\r\n#define INT64_MIN std::numeric_limits&lt;int64&gt;::min()\r\n#define UINT64_MIN std::numeric_limits&lt;uint64&gt;::min()\r\n#define UINT64_MAX std::numeric_limits&lt;uint64&gt;::max()\r\n#endif\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nThe following source files needed to include this header:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li> net.cpp</li>\r\n<li> wallet.cpp</li>\r\n<li> util.cpp</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n",
